entry.title: Unify AutofillProfile table layout.
entry.content:
kLocalOrSyncable and kAccount profiles are currently stored in sets of

tables with different layouts. This makes maintenance more difficult.

This CL migrates kLocalOrSyncable profiles to a new set of tables which

share the same layout as the kAccount profiles. See design doc in the

bug for more details.



This CL does several things, which sadly can't be split well:

- Create the new tables: local_profiles and local_profiles_type_tokens.

Since Sync support for kLocalOrSyncable profiles is about to be

sunset, "syncable" is not part of the table name.

- In the database migration logic, copy all existing kLocalOrSyncable

profiles from the old tables to the new ones. This is tested in

web_database_migration_unittest.cc.

- Adapt the AutofillTable CRUD functions to read/write from the new set

of tables. This amounts to parameterizing the existing reading/writing

functions for kAccount profiles. No new logic is added.

For this purpose, two helper functions GetProfileMetadataTable() and

GetProfileTypeTokensTable() are introduced. Since the unit tests are

already parameterized by profile source, no large changes are

necessary.

Much of the old logic that writes to the legacy tables becomes unused

and is removed. The reading functions are kept for the migration

logic.

entry.title: [Autofill] Remove relaxed shared-autofill Finch parameter
entry.content:
This CL removes the Finch parameter `relax_shared_autofill` introduced

in crrev.com/c/3500623. If enabled, `shared-autofill` was a sufficient

condition for cross-origin filling.



Without the parameter, a cross-origin field can only be filled if

`shared-autofill` is enabled and either

- the target origin is the main frame's origin and value to filled is

non-sensitive, or

- the triggered origin is the main frame's origin.

entry.title: Change clock drift samples distance to 1h
entry.content:
This CL does not have any functional consequences, it just decreases

noise of data we collect from clients in some UMA histograms.



Latency variance is currently a very large confounding factor for

analyzing the identifiable information leaked by the clock drift of

the user. Typical clock drift values lie around 1ms/s which means that

latency variances beyond 1ms2 will make the drift data completely

unreliable.



In this CL we change the distance between the clock skew samples used

for the computation of the drift to be 1h apart. This way, latency

variances in the order of milliseconds square will play a much

smaller role.

entry.title: Add switch to turn on 3P cookie blocking from command line
entry.content:
This switch is intended for testing purposes only and is not meant to

be enabled in production. It allows developers to test their sites

in order to adopt Privacy Sandbox APIs meant to replace third-party

cookies.



For now, the switch just enables 3PC blocking at startup and

overrides any changes to the 3P cookie blocking content setting.

Site-specific content settings can override this switch, which should

allow cookie access due to SAA.



When 3P cookie blocking is enabled, some Privacy Sandbox APIs are

disabled (e.g. FedCM). This is acceptable for now, but we should

iterate on this switch to enable these purpose-driven APIs and still

disables third-party cookie tracking.

entry.title: [FLEDGE] Store B&A auction result from response header Ad-Auction-Result
entry.content:
Add a `AdAuctionURLLoaderInterceptor` to monitor request & response:

1. Before making a network request (i.e. WillStartRequest()), if

the request is eligible for ad auction headers, add the

`Sec-Ad-Auction-Fetch: ?1` header.

2. If any redirect is encountered, skip handling the response; otherwise, for the response (i.e. OnReceiveResponse()), if the

previous request was eligible for ad auction headers, and if the

response header contains the auction result, store the auction

result (i.e. associate the auction result with the top-level page).



Explainer:

https://github.com/WICG/turtledove/blob/main/FLEDGE_browser_bidding_and_auction_API.md#step-3-get-response-blobs-to-browser

entry.title: css-multiple-display: Fix a crash with NGInlineNode::GetOffsetMapping()
entry.content:
For LayoutNGInlineListItem, we update its ordinal value in

CollectInlinesInternal(), and it might set NeedsLayout flag. So, we

should call SetNeedsCollectInlines() when the ordinal value is

invalidated.



We missed to call it. In that case,

1. A list item's style is changed. Ordinal values of other list items

are invalidated.

2. UpdateStyleAndLayoutForNode() at the beginning of innerText

processing missed to update the ordinal values.

3. NGInlineNode::GetOffsetMapping() calls CollectInlinesInternal(), and

it could set NeedsLayout flag. NGInlineNode::GetOffsetMapping() fails

if it is called again.
